`DeserializeFrom` does not work, unless you call `SerializeTo` on the syntax node at some point in your program beforehand. Looking at the source this is due to the `ObjectReader/Writer` sharing the same binder which only populates type readers on a write, but not on a read (it just errors).

From my IXmlSerializable wrapper:

```
public void WriteXml(XmlWriter writer)
{
    using (var ms = new MemoryStream())
    {
        Node.SerializeTo(ms);
        var buffer = new byte[ms.Length];

        ms.Position = 0;
        ms.Read(buffer, 0, buffer.Length);

        writer.WriteBase64(buffer, 0, buffer.Length); 

        // this works! But I don't want to do this at this point
        ms.Position = 0;
        var test = CSharpSyntaxNode.DeserializeFrom(ms);
    }
}
```

```
public void ReadXml(XmlReader reader)
{
    var encodedString = reader.Value;
    var buffer = Convert.FromBase64String(encodedString);
    using (var ms = new MemoryStream(buffer))
    {
        // this throws an InvalidOperationException! Unless WriteXml was called beforehand, 
        // which can't be guaranteed (nor should be needed)
        Node = CSharpSyntaxNode.DeserializeFrom(ms);
    }
}
```

